# Network Traffic Analysis 
## Objective
Analyze DNS and ICMP traffic logs to determine the cause of a network traffic issue.

## Context
This documentation was completed as part of the Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate program and was provided with tcmpdump traffic logs for analysis.

## Skills Demonstrated 
- DNS analysis
- ICMP analysis
- Incident investigation
- Documentation

## Tools Used
- Google Docs
- Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate

## Scenario
Several customers reported that they were not able to access the company website. I am tasked to analyze the given DNS and ICMP traffic logs to identify the cause of the website outage.

## Findings
The given UDP protocol logs revealed that port 53 is unreachable when attempting to access the website. The incident was suspected of being a DDoS attack.

## What I learned
This project helped me understand and learn how to perform:
- traffic log analysis
- Packet analysis
- Port 53
- Incident documentation
